# Day 1 SQL Notes

## SELECT

Show data from a table.

```sql id="ujtk0m"
SELECT * FROM Employees;
```

Show specific columns:

```sql id="aqnzho"
SELECT Name, salary
FROM Employees;
```

Alias:

```sql id="4jlwm3"
SELECT Name AS Employee_Name
FROM Employees;
```

---

## DISTINCT

Removes duplicate values.

```sql id="3dk3t9"
SELECT DISTINCT department
FROM Employees;
```

Unique combinations:

```sql id="b4h1ci"
SELECT DISTINCT department, salary
FROM Employees;
```

---

## WHERE

Filters rows.

```sql id="r1ylcf"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE department='IT';
```

```sql id="tpgjyz"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE salary > 50000;
```

Operators:

```text id="a8efvb"
=
>
<
>=
<=
!=
<>
```

---

## AND

Both conditions must be true.

```sql id="trr7qh"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE department='IT'
AND salary > 55000;
```

---

## OR

Any one condition can be true.

```sql id="63iy7k"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE department='HR'
OR department='Finance';
```

---

## IN

Short form of multiple ORs.

```sql id="13ixrx"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE department IN ('HR','Finance');
```

---

## BETWEEN

Range search.

```sql id="9d0ocg"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE salary BETWEEN 45000 AND 55000;
```

Includes both limits.

Equivalent to:

```sql id="vyn0hf"
WHERE salary >= 45000
AND salary <= 55000
```

---

## ORDER BY

Sort data.

Ascending:

```sql id="st9h08"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
ORDER BY salary ASC;
```

Descending:

```sql id="k0ef6m"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
ORDER BY salary DESC;
```

Multiple columns:

```sql id="vzt62g"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
ORDER BY department, salary DESC;
```

---

## LIMIT

Restricts number of rows returned.

First 2 rows:

```sql id="3kvw42"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
LIMIT 2;
```

Top 3 highest salaries:

```sql id="61q2y4"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
ORDER BY salary DESC
LIMIT 3;
```

---

## OFFSET

Skip rows.

```sql id="sntzdl"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
LIMIT 2 OFFSET 2;
```

Skip first 2 rows and return next 2.

---

## Most Important Interview Queries

Highest paid employee:

```sql id="njy85m"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
ORDER BY salary DESC
LIMIT 1;
```

Top 3 highest paid employees:

```sql id="u4x7d6"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
ORDER BY salary DESC
LIMIT 3;
```

Second highest paid employee:

```sql id="mqrf7k"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
ORDER BY salary DESC
LIMIT 1 OFFSET 1;
```

Unique departments:

```sql id="mr03p7"
SELECT DISTINCT department
FROM Employees;
```

IT employees:

```sql id="vwd2x3"
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE department='IT';
```

---

## Execution Order (Simplified)

```text id="b0ulul"
FROM
→ WHERE
→ SELECT
→ DISTINCT
→ ORDER BY
→ LIMIT
```

---

## Day 1 Cheat Sheet

```sql id="m43jgm"
SELECT * FROM table_name;

SELECT col1, col2 FROM table_name;

SELECT DISTINCT col1 FROM table_name;

SELECT * FROM table_name
WHERE condition;

SELECT * FROM table_name
WHERE condition1 AND condition2;

SELECT * FROM table_name
WHERE condition1 OR condition2;

SELECT * FROM table_name
WHERE col BETWEEN x AND y;

SELECT * FROM table_name
WHERE col IN (...);

SELECT * FROM table_name
ORDER BY col ASC;

SELECT * FROM table_name
ORDER BY col DESC;

SELECT * FROM table_name
LIMIT n;

SELECT * FROM table_name
LIMIT n OFFSET m;
```

